body:
Looks like `LayerNormalization`'s is wrongly [assigned to ONNX domain](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/463fac67a383611a507a0138a17e1403bd2cc04b/onnxruntime/core/graph/contrib_ops/contrib_defs.cc#L1970), so it doesn't appear in contrib ops' doc. Its domain should be changed to [kMSDomain](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/463fac67a383611a507a0138a17e1403bd2cc04b/onnxruntime/core/graph/contrib_ops/contrib_defs.cc#L792) for a fix. We should regenerate the document using [this flag](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/463fac67a383611a507a0138a17e1403bd2cc04b/tools/ci_build/build.py#L2413).

Just my record. The command used to update doc is
```
VERBOSE=1 ONNX_NAMESPACE=onnx CUDACXX=/usr/local/cuda-11.3/bin/nvcc ./build.sh --config Debug --use_cuda --cuda_home /usr/local/cuda-11.3 --cudnn_home /usr/local/cuda-11.3 --build_wheel --parallel --skip_tests --cmake_extra_defines CMAKE_CUDA_ARCHITECTURES=70 --cuda_version=11.3 --enable_nvtx_profile --cmake_extra_defines onnxruntime_DEBUG_NODE_INPUTS_OUTPUTS=ON --gen_doc 2>&1 |tee x.log
```

issue.title: Fix LayerNormalization's doc

issue.body:
LN's domain is wrong, so its doc is not
auto-generated. This PR fixes #10839.

body: @wschin does changing the domain impact usage compatibility for models?

It's possible. We wrongly put `LayerNormalization` in `ai.onnx` domain and generate several internal tests. If I correct the domain of `LayerNormalization`, those tests need to be updated to add `com.microsoft` domain. If end user inherit this incorrect assumption, their model will fail.

ORT has a backward compatibility guarantee, so let's keep it as-is. It does not impact anything other than cleanliness I think. 

Is there a reason it's not in ONNX? Can it be represented as a function? Related issue: https://github.com/onnx/onnx/issues/2379

It's a bit surprising ONNX doesn't include it... It can be defined as a ONNX function, so it's not expensive for backend to make it runnable. Given that ORT has a LayerNormation implementation with a function definition, we can easily add it to ONNX. 

I will close my PR. After some investigation, I realize it's an error back to 2020 and more than 70 tests are affected if we change LayerNormalization's domain... If it makes sense, this issue can be addressed by making `LayerNormalization` a formal ONNX op and therefore we can close this one.
Thanks. @wschin can you please propose the function in ONNX?

Yep. Just for future reference. This is a [link](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/a6ea278502e757049312eb6b11865a6bd2e7d07b/onnxruntime/core/graph/contrib_ops/contrib_defs.cc#L1969) to ORT's `LayerNormalization`.
Just a heads up. This is a [PR](https://github.com/onnx/onnx/pull/4076) for defining LayerNormalization in ONNX.
